Garvie, Robert Halley 

  Student U.C.D. [University College Dundee] 1891-1892 N. Phil.; Chem.; Prac. Chem.; Engin. Draw. 1892-1893 Inter. Math.; N. Phil.; Physics and Engin. Lab.; Jun. Engin.; Engin. Draw. 1893-1894 Physics; Sen. Engin.; Engin. Lab.; Engin. Draw. B.Sc. 30.3.1894.

  Born 30.6.1875 son of William Garvie, ironmonger, Perth and Marion Halley. Attended Perth Academy.

  Articled Manchester Ship Canal Company 1895-1898,
  then with various companies; 1900-1909 with Manchester Ship Canal company;
  1909-1912 in private practice and with Port of London Authority;
  1912-1913 assistant to W. H. Hunter, consulting engineer;
  1914-1919 chief engineer, Marine Board of Launceston, Tasmania;
  1919-1930 chief engineer, Messrs B. Morton & Sons, public works contractors, Manchester;
  1931-1941 Superintending engineer Cheshire County Council.[Engineer]
Died April, 1941.

